Pirates Copy Software Of Value Just For The Price Of A  Blank  Disk,  Which
Reduces Companies Profits And Gives Companies An Excuse To Charge Excessive
Prices For Their Games, Which As Often As Not, Are Crap !   If You Had Paid
Ł25 For A Crap Game Would You Be Happy ?    NO .... We  Are  Not  Condoning
Piracy, But There Are Two Sorts Of Pirate , Make Us Really Sick :

	      A : Those Who Charge Money For Pirated Software.

	      B : Those Who Pirate Software From Independent Sources,
		      i.e Not From Software Houses (Shareware e.t.c).

                        A Note To Software Houses :

Reduce Your Prices And Give All Computer Shops Playable Demos Of Your Games
So People Can TRY BEFORE THEY BUY. If You Do Not Want To Reduce Your Prices
An Excellent Way Around This Is To Include A Voucher For Ł5-Ł10 With  Every
Game You Sell So If Someone Buys One Of Your Games The Next One Will   Only
Cost About Ł15-Ł20 Depending On Its Original Price. So Only People That BUY
Your Games Will Get Them More Cheaply.
@EndNode
